comments.body:
@PaulHigin all I'm doing is passing the PSRP XML messages back and forth as a bytestream, the authentication/etc. still happens at the higher level (or within the application). I have it working great right now but for the client to connect you currently have to start "my" client and then enter-pshostsession to the named pipe it creates on the local machine. That's not a great user experience vs. something like just enter-pssession -customtransport websocat -argumentlist @{port=18522;host=my.websocat.server}
https://gist.github.com/JustinGrote/866536458bfa097cb18a4b82181e5f16

This is just a way to make it easily implemented and backwards compatible to 5.1. I suppose a powershell module might be able to implement a transport handler but I don't know how the scoping works there, ideas?

